	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>San Francisco</placeName> <date>July 7<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1862</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dr Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Yesterdays mail<lb/> brought me a letter from my son who<lb/> is one of the surgeons in the United States<lb/> Navy in which he mentions that He had<lb/> an introduction to you by <persName>Dr Fischel.</persName>  I<lb/> hope the interview was mutually agreeable<lb/> on his part I can answer for from the tone<lb/> in which he writes you being brought to mind<lb/> in this way I thought I would drop a few<lb/> lines&#44; altho&#39; I have nothing very particular<lb/> to relate.  Religious matters are at the stand<lb/> excepting that the Emanuel go on with<lb/> their reforms&#44; and their Rabbi is laboring<lb/> hard to set at <sic>nought</sic> all Orthodox <del>Refor</del><lb/> forms and ceremonies.  In a recent discourse<lb/> of his he stated that cutting the <add>Hebrew</add> over the<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add> is out of date and wearing the Beard<lb/> in the <add>Hebrew</add> is absurd.  The <add>&#63;</add> preached<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add> that is the real meaning<lb/> said the Preacher.  I was not present&#8212;but</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>such was the general reports.  It is pitiful<lb/> to relate how our sacred ceremonies are being<lb/> undermined.  It is currently reported that a<lb/> father brought his son to be taught the requisites<lb/> for his <add>Hebrew</add> but the Dr refused to teach<lb/> him to say <add>Hebrew</add> stating all was nonsense<lb/> I am however steadfast in my Orthodox<lb/> course and I am happy to say my <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> are firm with me.  That is one satisfaction to me<lb/> it was noticed last year that our <add>Hebrew</add> were<lb/> not as they should be.  I <add>&#63;</add> myself this<lb/> year in the matter&#44; and formed a party to<lb/> do as the Law directs and the result proved<lb/> as you will see by the enclosed Circular.<lb/>  It may not be of any moment to you so far<lb/> from us but in there perilous times every little<lb/> thing is of consequence to uphold the fabric<lb/> from falling into ruin.  No doubt you will think<lb/> with me.  I hope also to effect a radical reform<lb/> in the <add>Hebrew</add> of Heaven grant me strength and<lb/> health.  I have to fight the Battle in the good cause<lb/> I am at times sneered at being so old fashioned<lb/> and against progress <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> I say with <persName>David</persName> <add>Hebrew</add> and it must be<lb/> so in the end.  I amuse myself now when at<lb/> leisure in reading your Occident.  Will you<lb/> send me by return the following Nos. to complete<lb/> Vol. 18 of weekly series &#38; they are&#58; <hi rend="underline">1&#45;2&#45;3&#45;4&#45;5</hi><lb/> <hi rend="underline">20&#45;24&#45;27&#45;40&#45;42</hi> as also the whole volume <hi rend="underline">17</hi><lb/> so that I can bind them and you will oblige</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">Yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">H. A. Henry</persName></p>
				<p><hi rend="underline">Let me hear from you soon</hi>. </p>
		</body>
